    public abstract static class NetLoadable.NetLoadableService
extends NetLoadable
implements NetLoadableInterface.NetLoadableServiceInterface
    Interface name defined to make it easy to identify loadable services. Loadable services have no generic "run" interface - logically, they start when they are loaded. In practice, they may start threads when they are loaded (e.g., in their constructors), or loading them may simply make a set of methods available to other code (much like loading a library).
